The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     IN THE CITY
                  
	 Ballygunge United Club avoided relegation from the CAB first division league, crushing Barisha Sporting by 145 runs on Thursday. Barisha will now take on Tollygunge Agragami in a battle to avoid relegation.       
	SUMMARISED SCORES       
	Ballygunge United Club 379/9. Barisha Sporting 234 (Olive Chanda 86; Javed Anwar 4/75, Khagen Patra 3/38). Ballygunge United won by 145 runs.       
	Taltala Institute 294 (Abhishek Guha 67, Satyaki Biswas 66; Prabir Biswas 7/54). YMCA (College) 295/8 (Amal Das 137 n.o.; Subir Dey 4/118). YMCA won by 2 wkts.           
	 Mohun Bagan are seeking legal help to explore the possibility of signing Alvito DCunha. Alvito is understood to have given Mohun Bagan officials his contract paper with the red-and-gold outfit but the club are not keen on jumping the gun. Although Alvito has expressed a wish to play for Mohun Bagan, he still has two years of his contract with East Bengal to go.                 
	 All leading players cruised through their first two round matches in the 20th state age-group chess championships at the Bhowanipore Gujarati Education Society on Thursday.                 
	 St Johns thrashed FAPS 15-0 while Loreto Dharamtala beat Birla High 22-17 in the senior division of the WBAWB-organised inter-school basketball on Thursday.       
	RESULTS: Mini division: Loreto House C bt Loreto Dharamtala B 15-7; St Johns bt La Martiniere B 17-0. Jr. division: Loreto House bt La Martiniere B 30-11; Loreto Sealdah bt Park English 16-4. Sr. division: St Johns bt FAPS 15-0; Loreto Dharamtala bt Birla High 22-17.                 
	CHESS: Stage age-group meet: Round III at Bhowanipore Gujarati Education Society from 3pm.
                                                                                                                                                                     
